<p>Missouri presents an excellent opportunity for both solar energy adoption and HVAC system upgrades, making it an ideal state for homeowners looking to reduce energy costs and increase property value. With an average of 4.6 sun hours per day, Missouri receives sufficient solar irradiance to make solar panel installations financially viable across the state. The state's electricity rates average 11.2¬¢ per kWh, which is slightly below the national average, providing a solid baseline for calculating solar savings and return on investment.</p>

